  1‚Üí/**
  2‚Üí * FDC EVMTransaction Attestation Proof-of-Concept
  3‚Üí *
  4‚Üí * Verifies an Ethereum Sepolia transaction using Flare Data Connector (FDC)
  5‚Üí * via the @flarenetwork/flare-tx-sdk.
  6‚Üí *
  7‚Üí * Flow:
  8‚Üí * 1. Prepare attestation request via verifier API
  9‚Üí * 2. Submit attestation request to FdcHub on Coston2
 10‚Üí * 3. Wait for voting round finalization (poll DA layer)
 11‚Üí * 4. Fetch Merkle proof from Data Availability layer
 12‚Üí * 5. Verify proof on-chain via FdcVerification contract
 13‚Üí * 6. Validate and display transaction details
 14‚Üí *
 15‚Üí * What verification does (Merkle inclusion + on-chain root binding):
 16‚Üí * - The FdcVerification contract reconstructs the Merkle leaf from response data
 17‚Üí * - It computes the Merkle root using the provided proof path
 18‚Üí * - It checks that this computed root matches the root stored on-chain (in Relay contract)
 19‚Üí * - The on-chain root was signed by 50%+ of Flare's data providers
 20‚Üí * - This binds the attestation to Flare's consensus - if verification passes,
 21‚Üí *   the Sepolia transaction details are cryptographically proven correct
 22‚Üí */
 23‚Üí
 24‚Üíimport "dotenv/config";
 25‚Üíimport { ethers } from "ethers";
 26‚Üíimport { FdcSourceNetwork } from "@flarenetwork/flare-tx-sdk";
